cs.RO, cs.ED, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about a micro-scale mobile robot platform designed for robotics research and education.
- cs.ED (Education) is also likely as the platform is designed for educational purposes.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper describes the hardware and software architecture of the platform.
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is a possible category as the paper demonstrates the capabilities of the platform with several single- and multi-robot path and motion planning algorithms.
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a less likely category, but still possible as the platform utilizes 3D printing and maker culture.
